current_subtask:
  summary: Built a vendorless universal project remote and exposed its public projection as an active full-stack LIVE window inside the Sideways social product.
  directive:
    - no companies model names assigned minds permanent roles or mandatory choreography
    - every participant is an opaque temporary principal with granted capabilities
    - transport open-ended project payloads without pretending to understand their intelligence
    - keep messages append-only cursorable authenticated expiring and generation-bound
    - make current public work instantly visible to people and discoverable by programs
    - preserve the social product ranking corpus media profile starter and cleanup invariants
    - terminate only after exact-head proof direct phone inspection merge and honest deployment accounting
  completed:
    - added one generic Netlify remote endpoint backed by the existing Blob infrastructure
    - added HMAC bootstrap authentication and replaceable Ed25519 principals without company-specific identities
    - signed method path timestamp nonce and body digest and rejected stale timestamps replays duplicate ids expired credentials and insufficient capabilities
    - added generic read write claim release pause resume terminate admin repository CI and deployment capabilities
    - implemented append-only messages with application cursors and correct blob.key pagination over the installed Netlify Blobs API
    - added optional renewable releasable expiring claims over opaque scopes without enforcing turns
    - added session state blockers exact repository heads terminal proposals immutable terminal receipts and explicit new generations
    - added a vendorless command-line client for humans tools CI and future software
    - added a remote gate job that emits proceed pause stop superseded or terminal and gates later jobs through needs and if
    - preserved native GitHub concurrency cancellation as the authoritative stale-run mechanism
    - added machine discovery at .well-known/sideways-remote.json
    - added window.SidewaysRemote a sideways:remoteupdate event and a machine-readable public state output
    - mounted the visible LIVE control in owned title chrome so it never covers feed actions
    - exposed only public projections to browser code and kept signatures credentials private payloads and control authority server-side
    - made static builds truthfully use a repository snapshot while function-capable builds may opt into the live endpoint
    - preserved ordinary consumer labels and the profile-first social feed
    - detached video and audio sources before object URL revocation to eliminate intermittent media lifecycle failures
